Founder & CEO
member_experience_collection.description:
VIDA is a global platform that brings together creatives and manufacturers from around the world to create unique, original apparel and accessories - on-demand, at mass-scale. A curator of creative voices, VIDA showcases Art x Fashion from New York to LA, Mumbai to Madrid, and Tokyo to Tel Aviv. Our designers include world-renowned artists from 150+ countries around the world and our manufacturers range from textile mills to cut & sew units across India, Turkey, Pakistan, Sri Lanka, and more. We have launched over 2.5M unique products on our platform and have proudly partnered with the Museum of Modern Art (MOMA), DeYoung Museum, the iconic Cher, Steve Madden, WB Wonder Woman, and Iris Apfel.

Each of our products is custom-made, on-demand, and has a unique story - from the inspiration behind its design to the personal stories of our artists. For every product made, VIDA offers education and empowerment programs to our factory workers so they can build a better future for generations to come.

For every product made, VIDA enables education and empowerment programs to our factory workers so they can build a better future for generations to come. VIDA has donated over half a million meals to families in need in the United States, donated over thirty thousands masks to communities in need around the world, and committed over half a million dollars to support global education opportunities.
